<title type="html"><![CDATA[Forced Marriages - Shaykh `Abdur-Rahmaan as-Sa`dee [1375H]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1271&amp;p=1349#p1349"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Forced Marriages</span></strong><br /><em>Shaykh `Abdur-Rahmaan as-Sa`dee [1375H]</em><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Question:</span></strong><br /><br />Is it permissible to force one's daughter to marry someone she is not pleased with?<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Answer:</span></strong><br /><br />Her father cannot force her, nor can her mother force her to marry even if the both of them (i.e. mother and father) are pleased with his practice of the religion<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Shaykh `Abdur-Rahmaan as-Sa`dee</span></strong><br /><em>Al Majmoo'ah As-Sa'diyah vol. 7 p 349</em><br /><br />Translated by Abu Hakeem Bilal Davis<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.fatwaislam.com/fis/index.cfm?scn=fd&amp;ID=487">http://www.fatwaislam.com/fis/index.cfm?scn=fd&amp;ID=487</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> â€” Fri Mar 10, 2017 11:35 pm</p><hr />
